What is a Clustered Index vs Non-Clustered Index?
 Clustered Index:

Sorts and stores table data physically in the index order.

Only one clustered index per table (because data can only be sorted one way).

 Non-Clustered Index:

Creates a separate structure that points to the actual data.

Can have multiple non-clustered indexes per table.

 Example:

CREATE CLUSTERED INDEX idx_emp_id ON Employee(emp_id);
CREATE NONCLUSTERED INDEX idx_emp_name ON Employee(emp_name);
